          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2020-02-24T18:40:52Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Recovering Excessive Funds for Unused and Needless Drugs Act of 2019 or the REFUND Act of 2019</b></p> <p>This bill requires drug manufacturers to issue rebates to the Centers for Medicare &amp; Medicaid Services (CMS) in relation to discarded amounts (i.e., amounts remaining after administration) of single-dose vial drugs that are covered under Medicare. Manufacturers that fail to comply are subject to civil penalties.</p> <p>The CMS must determine rebate amounts based on payment claims from providers. (Currently, providers may receive payment under Medicare for discarded amounts of single-dose vial drugs through the use of a specific claims modifier.)</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2019-08-09T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
